   {
    "text": "A Samurai is a hereditary military position. They are well paid warriors and retainers to a Daimyō, and enjoy high prestige and special privilege. Samurai are formally ordained through the granting of a Katana and Wakizashi. Samurai must follow the rules of Bushido or risk being cast down as dishonorable, and expected to commit Seppuku through Hara-Kiri. In the Edo period, Samurai also serve in managerial roles throughout their Daimyō's estate and are well educated. Ronin are Samurai that do not serve a Daimyō.",
    "contextConfig": {
     "suffix": "\n",
     "tokenBudget": 2048,
     "budgetPriority": -400
    },
    "displayName": "Samurai",
    "keys": [
